.TH objectremove
.SH NAME
objectremove - command for removing data from the game objects.
.SH DESCRIPTION
With objectremove you can remove data like items, effects, skills, quests and flags from the game objects.
.SH OPTIONS
.P
* item
.br
objectremove -o item -t [object ID]#[object serial]... -a [item ID]#[item serial]
.br
Removes specified item from the inventory of each target object.
.br
All target arguments need to be IDs and serial values of existing objects connected
with '#'[hash].
.br
The argument needs to be the ID and serial value of the item to remove connected with '#'[hash].
.br
Example:
.br
objectremove -o item -t char1#0 char1#1 -a itemSword1#0
.P
* effect
.br
objectremove -o effect -t [object ID]#[object serial]... -a [effect ID]#[effect serial]
.br
Removes specified effect from each target object.
.br
All target arguments need to be IDs and serial values of existing objects connected
with '#'[hash].
.br
The argument needs to be the ID and serial value of the effect to remove connected with '#'[hash].
.br
Example:
.br
objectremove -o effect -t char1#0 char1#1 -a bleed1#0
.P
* skill
.br
objectremove -o skill -t [object ID]#[object serial]... -a [skill ID]
.br
Removes specified skill from each target object.
.br
All target arguments need to be IDs and serial values of existing objects connected
with '#'[hash].
.br
The argument needs to be the ID of the skill to remove.
.br
Example:
.br
objectremove -o skill -t char1#0 char1#1 -a fireball1
.P
* quest
.br
objectremove -o quest -t [object ID]#[object serial]... -a [quest ID]
.br
Removes specified quest from the journal of each target object.
.br
All target arguments need to be IDs and serial values of existing objects connected
with '#'[hash].
.br
The argument needs to be the ID of the quest to remove.
.br
Example:
.br
objectremove -o quest -t char1#0 char1#1 -a quest1
.P
* flag
.br
objectremove -o flag -t [object ID]#[object serial]... -a [flag ID]
.br
Removes specified flag from each target object.
.br
All target arguments need to be IDs and serial values of existing objects connected
with '#'[hash].
.br
The argument needs to be the ID of the flag to remove.
.br
Example:
.br
objectremove -o flag -t char1#0 char1#1 -a testFlag
.SH SEE ALSO
objectadd, objectset, objectshow, objecthave, objectuse
